AI agents advance atomic force microscopy automation: new benchmark reveals capabilities and critical safety concerns<\/a><\/h2>\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>New research published in Nature Communications by Mandal et al. (Indian Institute of Technology Delhi, India) presents a comprehensive evaluation of large language model agents for automating atomic force microscopy. The researchers developed AILA (Artificially Intelligent Lab Assistant) and AFMBench to assess the potential and limitations of AI-powered laboratory automation. Atomic force microscopy (AFM) is\u2026<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"entry-meta\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-11-20T10:34:28+01:00\">20 November 2025<\/time><time class=\"updated\" datetime=\"2025-11-20T10:35:29+01:00\">20 November 2025<\/time>\t\t\t\t<\/div><!-- .entry-meta -->\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div><!-- .entry-wrapper -->\n\t<\/article>\n\n\t\t\n\t<article data-post-id=\"3003\"\n\t\tclass=\"category-conferences-events type-post post-has-image\"\n\t\t\t\t>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure class=\"post-thumbnail\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"\/2025\/11\/05\/hackaton-ai-and-ml-for-microscopy\/\" rel=\"bookmark\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"988\" height=\"284\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/smartmicroscopy.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/11\/hackaton.png?fit=988%2C284&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"attachment-newspack-article-block-uncropped size-newspack-article-block-uncropped wp-post-image\" alt=\"Hackaton: AI and ML for Microscopy\" data-hero-candidate=\"1\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/smartmicroscopy.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/11\/hackaton.png?w=988&amp;ssl=1 988w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/smartmicroscopy.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/11\/hackaton.png?resize=300%2C86&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/smartmicroscopy.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/11\/hackaton.png?resize=768%2C221&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" data-atta